    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In the scale chapter we said a scale is a set of intervallic relationships. Major: W-W-H-W-W-W-H; each mode has its own. Likewise, chords—built from several notes—have their own intervallic recipes, which determine their character and name."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Take C E G for example:"
        }
      ]
    },
